"When I'm troubled,"

547
00:42:00,041 --> 00:42:02,040
"she's all tears."

548
00:42:02,208 --> 00:42:04,540
"In my joy, too,"

549
00:42:04,541 --> 00:42:06,790
"her tears wet her scarf."

550
00:42:06,875 --> 00:42:09,165
"With every tear drop,"

551
00:42:09,166 --> 00:42:11,499
"she weaves blessings."

552
00:42:11,500 --> 00:42:16,915
"Will someone tell me, are all moms like this?"

553
00:42:19,458 --> 00:42:28,332
"Sometimes she's practical,
and sometimes she's emotional."

554
00:42:28,541 --> 00:42:37,290
"Her one smile, dispels all my worries."

555
00:42:37,625 --> 00:42:46,499
"She's like a master key,
which opens all the locks to my fortunes."

556
00:42:46,583 --> 00:42:55,624
"I've placed in her care,
all my trunks, full of dreams."

557
00:42:55,708 --> 00:42:59,874
"My dearest mom."

558
